read_codesign_die_abstract(25.10)            read_codesign_die_abstract(25.10)

Name
       read_codesign_die_abstract  - Reads the die abstract directly to update
       Innovus

Syntax
       read_codesign_die_abstract

       [-help]

       DIEABSTRACTFILE

       [-check_only]

       [-no_diff]

       Reads the die abstract directly to update Innovus. The command provides
       flexibility in terms of what is read and the elimination of the I/O Up-
       date file and TCL code.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each read_codesign_die_abstract parameter. For a
              detailed  description  of the command and all of its parameters,
              use the man command:

              man read_codesign_die_abstract

       <DIEABSTRACTFILE>
              Specifies the name of the die abstract file.

       -check_only
              This is only valid with the -no_diff option. If  these  two  op-
              tions  are  given,  then the difference viewer will not be used,
              and the Innovus db will not be updated.

       -no_diff
              When the -no_diff option is used, the difference viewer will not
              be utilized. The die abstract will be read and  the  Innovus  db
              will be updated with all the changes unless the  -check_only op-
              tion is provided.

Related Information
